config:        contain database and server config files.
controller:    js contain , flow of data, view and model .
middleware:    for authentication and validation
migration :    any change of database recorded and sync through this command 
model :        files by ORM , Schema and Querey
node_modules:  all the NPM (node package manger ) installed 
route:         make api calls to database , listen on port , end point
seeder :       its like meta data , provide  data to database 
services:      files with business logic used to access dbase 
.env:           all the password and name , hostname
package.json :  all the dependencies all the framework version u can see 

 API Call --> Routes --> Controller(handle data) --> service <--> dbase 
migration follow DDL (Data Definition lang)


